Facebook Hires Dentsu as Marketing Representative in Japan

-- B y   J u n   Y a n g
-- 
2011-02-28T09:07:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/facebook-hires-dentsu-as-marketing-representative-in-japan-1-.html
Facebook Inc. hired  Dentsu Inc .,
Japan’s largest advertising company, to be its sales and
marketing representative in the nation as the world’s biggest
social-networking site expands there.  Dentsu will provide consulting services for companies that
want to use Facebook for advertising and marketing, the Japanese
company said in a statement. Dentsu will have exclusive rights
to sell space on Facebook’s premium ad service for one year,
according to the statement.  Facebook, which is based in  Palo Alto , California, and has
more than 500 million users, is focusing on expansion in Japan
and Russia, Chief Executive Officer Mark Zuckerberg said in July.
The site has almost doubled its number of users in Japan to
about 2.6 million in the past six months, according to market
researcher  Socialbakers .  Facebook opened an office in Japan in September.  A call to Kumiko Hidaka, a Facebook spokeswoman in  California , was not answered Monday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jun Yang in Seoul at 
